org.sakaiproject.memory.impl

Class GenericMultiRefCacheImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sakaiproject.memory.impl.MemCache
      • org.sakaiproject.memory.impl.GenericMultiRefCacheImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Observer, net.sf.ehcache.event.CacheEventListener, org.sakaiproject.memory.api.Cache, org.sakaiproject.memory.api.Cacher, org.sakaiproject.memory.api.GenericMultiRefCache
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MultiRefCacheImpl

    public class GenericMultiRefCacheImpl
extends MemCache
implements org.sakaiproject.memory.api.GenericMultiRefCache, net.sf.ehcache.event.CacheEventListener

    MultiRefCacheImpl implements the MultiRefCache.

    The references that each cache entry are sensitive to are kept in a separate map for easy access.
    Manipulation of this map is synchronized. This map is not used for cache access, just when items are added and removed.
    The cache map itself becomes synchronized when it's manipulated (not when reads occur), so this added sync. for the refs fits the existing pattern.
